The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 A petition was filed by Calcutta Municipal Corporation (CMC) on Thursday before the division bench of Chief Justice V.S. Sirpurkar, seeking leave for filing an appeal against the order of Justice G.C. Gupta, who had held civic commissioner Debashis Som guilty of contempt of court. 

 he plea was granted. The appeal petition will be heard by the division bench of Justice A.K. Chakraborty and Justice S.P. Talukdar on Friday.

 Ramnath Ram, 45, was knocked down by a taxi at the crossing of New Road and Mayo Road on Thursday morning. He was taken to SSKM Hospital, where his condition was stated to be critical. The taxi driver could not be traced. 

 The undergraduate council of Calcutta University on Thursday ordered an inquiry into the allegation that Charuchandra College was offering a post graduate diploma course in microbio technology that was not recognised by the university. The charge has been brought by a section of students of the college. A university official said the college was not authorised to offer such a course.

 A CID team recovered an astadhatu figurine of Lord Govinda, believed to have been stolen from Cooch Behar Rajbari, from an antique dealer on Wednesday.

 he sleuths, posing as customers, had asked the dealer to come to Diamond Harbour with his collection. However, during bargaining, the dealer sensed danger and left the place with all but one antique ? the 3.5 gram figurine.

 The two owners of a medicine shop were arrested on Wednesday night on the charge of selling drugs after their expiry date had lapsed. The complaint against Amiya Medical Centre, in Howrah?s Belgachhia, was lodged by Kajal Sarkar, a local resident. 

